<div class="StaticPagesController">
  <div class="container">

    <h1>How to Contribute</h1>

      <p>
        <strong>The Odin project</strong> is crowdsourced and built by people learning to code,
        <em>just like you</em>. You can contribute too, in fact we hope you do! Even if you
        don't feel ready, you can still get involved and observe until you're comfortable. Still
        not sure? Here are some <a id="reasonsToggle" href="#reasonsModal" data-toggle = "modal">reasons to get
        involved!</a>
      </p>

            <div id="reasonsModal" class="modal hide fade" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="reasonsModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
              <div class="modal-header">
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-hidden="true">x</button>
                <h3 id="reasonsModalLabel">Contributing</h3>
              </div>

              <div class="modal-body" style="background: #666;color: white;font-size: .75em">
                <p >The Odin Project is designed around a simple idea- make it easy for you to
                    get started coding! We want to make it easy for newcomers to get into an
                    <em>actual</em> real-world coding environment so you can get the experience
                    you need. <strong>Here's the benefits to you:</strong>
                </p>
                <ul>
                  <li>Flexibility! You can work on your own time. It's not 9 to 5 so you can
                      get involved when it's convenient for you.</li>
                  <li>Exposure! Contributors to The Odin Project will be listed on the page
                      and on github, where you can show people your work!</li>
                  <li>Relevant Training! This is the development that is in demand and
                      happening today.</li>
                  <li>Job Focus! No matter why you are learning to code, the right skills matter.
                      You'll learn good habits and discipline that will put you at the top.</li>
                  <li>Community! Meet like-minded people and start building your network now.
                      Find others that can work in your schedule and interests.</li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div class="modal-footer">
                <h3>But mostly... it's fun!</h3>
              </div>
            </div>

    <h2>Where do I start?</h2>

      <p><em>If you have a completed project you'd like to add, go <a href="#">here.</a>
             Otherwise, start by choosing your skill level:</em></p>

        <div class="container">
          <div class="row-fluid">
            <div class="span2">
              <%=image_tag "icons/star1.png", title: "Beginner"%>
            </div>
            <div class="span10" style="padding-top: 0;">
              <h2 style="margin-top:.75em;">Total Newbie</h2>

                <p>
                  If you're just learning to program, this is where to start. Click below to see
                  your paths, and check out the Contributor's Hall of Fame at the bottom of the
                  page- that's your goal!
                </p>
            </div>
            <div style="text-align:center;">
              <span id="moreButton" style="color:#f90; cursor: pointer;" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#newbie-path">More</span>
            </div>
          </div>
            <div id="newbie-path" class="row-fluid collapse">
              <div class="span6">
                <h3>The Courses</h3>
                <div style="font-size:.75em; height:400px; background:#666; color:white; padding:5px">
                  <p>
                    You should begin by working through the curriculum from the start. It will
                    take some time, but it is worth the effort. Don't cut corners. There is a
                    steep learning curve at first, you will get better. Stick with it, work with
                    others, and set goals. The study groups are a great place to get involved!
                  </p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Complete the 'On-Boarding' section on this page</li>
                    <li>
                      Set up a <%= link_to "Github account", "http://github.com"%>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Check out the <%= link_to "study group", studygroup_path %>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Start on the <%= link_to "courses", curriculum_path %>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Write a lot of code!
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
              <div class="span6">
                <h3>Observer/Bug Sniper</h3>
                <div style="font-size:.75em; height:400px; background:#666; color:white; padding:5px">
                  <p>
                    You can begin to get involved with the project by observing and even bug sniping!
                    Watch our pair programming events (many are recorded) and see how the developers
                    are building code. You can also work by pairing with other students going through
                    the course!
                  </p>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Complete the 'On-Boarding' section on this page</li>
                    <li>
                      Set up a <%= link_to "Github account", "http://github.com"%>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Fork the main and dev branches from the <%= link_to "Repo", "https://github.com/TheOdinProject/theodinproject" %>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Set up an account on <%= link_to "Pivotal Tracker", "http://pivotaltracker.com" %>
                    </li>

                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
        </div>

		<div class="container">
