		<div id="onboarding">
		  <h2>On-Boarding</h2>
		  <p>
		    The purpose of on-boarding is for you to get up to speed on the project and how it is
		    managed, as well as familiarize yourself with several of the tools and websites
		    used by the team. You should read the following pages as well as sign up at a few
		    necessary sites, as listed here:
		  </p>
		  <ul>
		    <li>
		      First, read the <a href="https://github.com/TheOdinProject/theodinproject/blob/master/getting_involved.md">"Getting Involved"</a> document for a detailed overview and instructions on how to proceed.
		    </li>
		    <li>
		      Set up a <a href="http://github.com">Github Account</a> if you haven't yet
		    </li>
		    <li>
		      Set up an account on <a href="http://pivotaltracker.com">Pivotal Tracker</a> 
		    </li>
		    <li>
		      Many people working in open source software work on Macs or linux. On Windows, a vm running Linux is probably best.
		    </li>
		    <li>
		      Join us on our <%= link_to "Google Community", "https://plus.google.com/communities/100013596437379837846" %>
		    </li>

		  </ul>
		</div>


		  <h2>CONTACT</h2>
		  <p>
		    Check out our <%= link_to "Google Community", "https://plus.google.com/communities/100013596437379837846" %> for discussions and events around those efforts, as well as additional links for learning more about this living and growing adventure we call The Odin Project.
		  </p>
